## Fix-stories (from gates — NOT in `{{PLAN}}`; run first, must clear before the epic gate closes)

The `source:` pointer is **load-bearing: it is the only place the fix-story's acceptance criteria exist.** The orchestrator builds it from the gate's *return* alone (which is why every gate must return findings **numbered** with its report filename) and never opens the report. The scoper resolves the pointer; if it cannot, it **refuses to scope rather than invent AC**.

### <EPIC-ID>
- `[pending]` **F-XX.1** <one-line title> — source: `{{REVIEWS_DIR}}code-review-<EPIC-ID>.md`, finding #3 [blocker]
- `[done]` **F-XX.2** <one-line title> — source: `{{REVIEWS_DIR}}regression-<EPIC-ID>-r1.md`, finding #1 — commit `<hash>`

(empty if none)

**Termination bound:** if the same failing test survives two fix-story → `regression-run` cycles, **stop**. Mark it `blocked`, record every fix-story tried and why each did not clear it. Two failed attempts at the same red means the diagnosis is wrong, and a third fix-story will not find it.

